                <head>245. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>From March 21 to 23, 1957, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> and Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName> met with Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Macmillan</persName> and Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LS1"
                        >Lloyd</persName> at the Mid-Ocean Club in Bermuda. Their extensive
                    discussions touched upon the question of China policy at several points. These
                    discussions are scheduled for publication in the United Kingdom compilation in a
                    forthcoming volume.</p>
            </div>
